Template: snapweb/patch_config
Type: boolean
Description: Patch snapserver configuration?
 The configuration parameter "http/doc_root" in "/etc/snapserver.conf" must point to "/usr/share/snapweb".

Template: snapweb/change_config
Type: note
Description: Please change your Snapserver configuration
 To activate Snapweb, you need to change your Snapserver configuration 
 (usually located at /etc/snapserver.conf) to point to Snapweb.
  
 Change the "doc_root" parameter in the "[http]" section to
 "doc_root = /usr/share/snapweb" and restart the snapserver.
 